rComments: He's an awesome professor! I had no programming experience and I had no trouble passing the class. Read the book, go to class and go to lab and you'll pass. He was flexible with deadlines if enough people complained about the due date of hw. No midterm but had 5 quizzes instead. Quizzes were easy but the final was nothing like them so study!

Mr. Whitehead will assign complicated programs as homework with very little explanation or help. He has no sympathy for students' progress, and is very unclear. He will briefly brush over topics and then dive into complicated code examples. Most of class time is spent waiting for clicker questions to be over; he spends too long on clicking in.

His manner of teaching is not friendly to non-CS major. He is very tough on deadlines but you won't see a grade before 6th week of school. He is also unable to control the class. It is weird that as a tech savvy person, he refuses to use the app for iClicker. Also read the code and the book, do not rely on lec. I would not recommend the professor.
The dudes just freaking weird and tries to make class entertaining but it's just annoying, also he loves to give trick questions ALL THE TIME!

Uses iClicker for attendance and to see where students might be confused. Not the best professor, but personable in office hours, and gradually became a better professor through the quarter. First assignments were assigned in a sloppy way, but got better. Drops lowest assignment grade. Puts an effort towards making the class interactive.

Funny, engaging, and very good at explaining algorithms and data structures in a clear, concise way. Takes the time to use a lot of visuals and in class group exercises to make CS fun, interactive, and social! He's innovative and unafraid to teach CS in a new way. He uses RPG elements in the class to tell stories and encourage participation.

Awesome teacher! Incorporated RPGs into class participation grades, let students work out examples and participate in lectures. Really engaging lectures, even in a class with hundreds of students. Adorable pink glasses!

Took his class over the summer. Read the book, review the in-class examples, go to the sections. The assignments may be better worded.  I-clicker quizzes help you to understand the material and helps you to engage during the lecture.

Nathan was an excellent professor, he came to class prepared and adjusted his pace to deal with the difficulties some students were having. A couple times he glossed over things that were second nature to him that weren't immediately obvious to the rest of us, but he always went back and made sure we understood everything. Really enjoyed his class!

Professor Whitehead is a good teacher if you're familiar with programming. Otherwise, he's a little insensitive to those who are taking this class without any prior knowledge of programming. Go to labs and ask for help when you're confused, TAs are super nice.
He's great just go to labs and remember to look up stuff online

He's pretty boring and weird (for example showed us memesdoge meme stuff). A lot of the stuff can be dense when it comes to the actual coding that you do on the programs. He tries to incorporate history and there is an essay about privacy you have to do, and it is peer graded. HW was difficult bc he can't really teach the coding part that well.

Cool professor! Made clans for the class and gave a lot of quizzes to engage participation. We had to use our i-clickers. But great class! We didn't have to go to lab - he shared a lot of resources such as x2go where we could run the unix lab at ucsc on our laptops remotely. He's fun and teaches using a lot of examples and runs codes in class.

It's rare to take a computer science class where the lectures keep your attention throughout the entire 70 minutes. He really tries to keep students interested, and lays out the rather complex material very clearly. Good at explaining things. Tests and assignments can be rough, but this is true of pretty much any comp sci class.

He is an awesome professor, the only things that hurt me were the midterms and the final. I would study so hard and still wouldn't do so hot on the test. The assignments are tough but find a good partner and you are good! His teaching style is great though and he is a very smart man. The labs were fun and I got a A- in that.

Whitehead's lectures are long, but they're clear and interesting. He teaches the material thoroughly. If you go to section they will pretty much tell you how to do the assignment. He does clickers everyday, so if you miss class you lose participation points.

The teacher is creative.  He tells very detailed stories and gives you 'exp'   for class participation. The lectures are good and informative. I enjoyed going to his lectures and they passed by quick. The only problem I had with the class were the assignments because he does not go over must of the language so you will struggle if you suck at java.
